Former Bafana Bafana skipper Neil Tovey sends his condolences to the Batchelor family following Marc's untimely death. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tributes continue to pour in for former footballer Marc Batchelor. He was gunned down outside his Olivedale home in northern Johannesburg on Monday. READ: Two suspects sought for Marc Batchelor's murder "Marc was very passionate about the game. Everybody that knew him, knows that he was a very kind person," said his former teammate, Neil Tovey. Police have opened an investigation into the motive behind the murder and no arrests have been made as of yet.